README.md

Awesome

   [https://gitter.im/awesome-information-retrieval/Lobby?utm_source=badge
   &utm_medium=badge&utm_campaign=pr-badge&utm_content=badge]Join the chat
   at https://gitter.im/awesome-information-retrieval/Lobby

   Curated list of information retrieval and web search resources from all
   around the web.

Introduction

   [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Information_retrieval]Information
   Retrieval involves finding relevant information for user queries,
   ranging from simple domain of database search to complicated aspects of
   web search (Eg - Google, Bing, Yahoo). Currently, researchers are
   developing algorithms to address
   [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Information_needs]Information Need of
   user(s), by maximizing
   [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Relevance_(information_retrieval)]User
   and Topic Relevance of retrieved results, while minimizing
   [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Information_overload]Information
   Overload and retrieval time.

Contributing

   Please feel free to send me
   [https://github.com/harpribot/awesome-information-retrieval/pulls]pull
   requests or [email]
   (mailto:[mailto:harshal.priyadarshi@utexas.edu]harshal.priyadarshi@utex
   as.edu) me to add new links. I am very open to suggestions and
   corrections. Please look at the
   [file://localhost/harpribot/awesome-information-retrieval/blob/master/c
   ontributing.md]contributions guide.

