Talks

Technical Talks

     * [https://youtu.be/1X71fTx1LKA]Extreme Classification: A New
       Paradigm for Ranking & Recommendation - Manik Verma (Microsoft
       Research)
     * [https://www.ted.com/talks/tim_berners_lee_on_the_next_web]The next
       web - Tim Berners-Lee (Ted Talk) [Tim Berners-Lee invented the
       World Wide Web. He leads the World Wide Web Consortium (W3C),
       overseeing the Web's standards and development].
     * [https://www.ted.com/talks/gary_flake_is_pivot_a_turning_point_for_
       web_exploration?utm_source=tedcomshare&utm_medium=referral&utm_camp
       aign=tedspread]Is Pivot a turning point for web exploration? - Gary
       Flake, Technical Fellow at Microsoft (TED Talks).
     * [http://videolectures.net/wsdm09_dean_cblirs/]Challenges in
       Building Large-Scale Information Retrieval Systems - Jeff Dean
       (WSDM Conference, 2009).
     * [https://youtu.be/NFCZuzA4cFc]Knowledge-based Information Retrieval
       with Wikipedia - David Wilne (The University of Waikato, 2008).
     * [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SghMq1xBJPI&list=PLdktw5AjQqP2gpQN
       gHRJaSgEkHiaVLfTi&index=24]Music Information Retrieval Using
       Locality Sensitive Hashing - Steve Tjoa (RackSpace Developers)
       [This talk shows that IR is not just text and images].
     * [https://youtu.be/u6oqr3gMyxk]The Functional Web -- The Future of
       Apps and the Web - Liron Shapira (Box Tech Talk).
     * [https://youtu.be/EnvtsbCfiAI]Information Experience - Solution to
       Information Overload on Web - Doug Imbruce (Techcrunch
       Disrupt)[Doug Imbruce is the Founder of Qwiki, Inc, a technology
       startup in New York, NY, acquired by Yahoo! in 2013].
     * [https://youtu.be/tnsyhKHalGs]Internet Privacy - Dr. Alma Whitten
       (Google Brussels Tech Talk).

Philosophical Talks

     * [https://www.ted.com/talks/andreas_ekstrom_the_moral_bias_behind_yo
       ur_search_results]The moral bias behind your search results -
       Andreas Ekström (Swedish Author & Journalist, TED Talk).
     * [https://www.ted.com/talks/eli_pariser_beware_online_filter_bubbles
       ?language=en]Beware online "filter bubbles" - Eli Pariser (Author
       of the Filter Bubble, TED Talk).
     * [https://www.ted.com/talks/andy_yen_think_your_email_s_private_thin
       k_again]Think your email's private? Think again - Andy Yen (CERN,
       TED Talk) [This talk talks about privacy, which Search Engines
       intrude into, and how can people protect it].
     * [https://youtu.be/YO0lbdhF30g]Do we have the right to be forgotten?
       - Michael Douglas [TEDx SouthBank].
     * [https://www.ted.com/talks/christopher_m00t_poole_the_case_for_anon
       ymity_online?utm_source=tedcomshare&utm_medium=referral&utm_campaig
       n=tedspread]The case for anonymity online - Christopher "moot"
       Poole" (Ted Talks) [Christopher "moot" Poole is founder of 4chan,
       an online imageboard whose anonymous denizens have spawned the
       web's most bewildering and influential subculture].

